  "source_text": "و أقول يا إلهي بأنّك أنت عارف أُشاهد بأنّ مظاهر العرفان قد خلقت بأمرك ولو أقول بأنّك أنت حكيم أُشاهد بأنّ مطالع الحكمة قد ذوّتت بإرادتك وإن قلتُ بأنّك أنت الفرد أُلاحظ بأنّ حقايق التّفريد قد بعثت بإنشائك وإن قلتُ إنّك أنت العليم أُشاهد بأنّ جواهر العلم قد حقّقت بمشيّ",
  "translation": "If I describe Thee, O my God, as Him Who is the All-Perceiving, I find myself compelled to admit that They Who are the highest Embodiments of perception have been created by virtue of Thy behest. And if I extol Thee as Him Who is the All-Wise, I, likewise, am forced to recognize that the Wellsprings of wisdom have themselves been generated through the operation of Thy Will. And if I proclaim Thee as the Incomparable One, I soon discover that they Who are the inmost essence of oneness have been sent down by Thee and are but the evidences of Thine handiwork. And if I acclaim Thee as the Knower of all things, I must confess that they Who are the Quintessence of knowledge are but the creation and instruments of Thy Purpose.",
